  "body": "Hi all,\r\n\r\nThis is part of #1284. According to the spec and the [document](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1-4ct3v7O9dRiYZXqMO3lO6V3MqZd3Aa881CsagwAGVI/edit#) put together by the Pegasys team regarding deposit processing: \r\n\r\nEvery DEPOSIT_ROOT_VOTING_PERIOD / EPOCH_LENGTH epochs (1024/64 = 16 epochs) \r\na check is done. If a deposit root has received over half of the available votes during the \r\nlast epoch we put it into the stateâ€™s latest_deposit_root and clear the candidate deposit root list.\r\n\r\nA PR would implement the logic above in the `blockchain` service to update the state accordingly. It is recommended to use a Mutex here to prevent any other updates to state during the setting of the latest_deposit_root.",
